com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.managers

Class UpdateManagerRequestExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.RequestExecutor<java.lang.String>
      • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.managers.UpdateManagerRequestExecutor

  • public class UpdateManagerRequestExecutor
extends RequestExecutor<java.lang.String>
    Request executor provided by ManagersApi. Use this class if you want to update managers through fluent API in chained fashion, for instance: 
       
   KontaktCloud kontaktCloud = KontaktCloudFactory.create();
   Manager updatedManager = new Manager.Builder()
      .email("admin.kontakter@kontakt.io")
      .role(Manager.Role.ADMIN)
      .build();
   kontaktCloud.managers().update(ID)
      .with(updatedManager)
      .execute();
